node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Pregnancy Style 💙 on September 13, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and text that says '10 Before 9 months Pregnant pregnancy 6 weeks Postpartum'.

node.text:
Last time I posted my before and after photo, I got a lot of comments and messages saying it was photoshopped or unrealistic in different pages but as I said last time, everyone’s journey is different and everyone’s body is different. I’m not sure if you want to call it good genes or saying I’m just lucky but I can tell you it comes down to choosing healthy diet, being active during and before pregnancy and healthy lifestyle. It has nothing to do with luck! I also found out that there are two types of people, one that see these photos and find it inspiring and encouraging and others who want to bring you down and call it fake so they make themselves feel better! Choose a healthy diet and a healthy lifestyle 🙏🏼you’ll feel better physically and mentally. 

.
Repost from @niyoosha.insta .
#pregnantandperfect #pregnancy #bump #babygirl #babygirlnursery #babygirl #postpartumbody #pregnantandperfect #6weeksold #postbabybody #babyphoto #6weekspostpartum #mums #mumslife #mumsandbubs #fitmum #fitpregnancy

To the first positive line on the pregnancy test.⁣
⁣
To that first appointment, and hearing your perfect heartbeat loud and clear.⁣
⁣
To the first ultrasound, and seeing you wiggle on the screen. ⁣
⁣
To the changes that my body went through, as you grew inside of me. ⁣
⁣
To hearing your first cry, and seeing you take your first breath in this world.⁣
⁣
After 9 months of growing and anxiously waiting for you, I can’t believe that you are finally here my baby! ❤️
